[5] Russia (Udmurtia ex Thailand)
Date: Tue 24 Apr 2012
Source: Dyen [in Russian, machine trans. edited]
http://www.dayudm.ru/news/2012/04/24/51989/


According to the Rospotrebnadzor of the Udmurt Republic, on 23 Apr 2012, a significantly increased number of suspected measles cases was recorded in Izhevsk involving tourists from Thailand. A total of 27 suspected cases of measles were admitted to hospital. Of these, 12 have been confirmed as measles cases by laboratory diagnosis, and the outcome of testing the remaining 15 are awaited. Earlier, it had been reported that as many as 16 local people had contracted measles, all inhabitants of the capital of Udmurtia and of the Zavyalovskogo area. 3/4ths of them were adults aged 19 to 47 years. Five cases were children of preschool age. The number of citizens of the republic exposed to carriers of infection was estimated to be 3200 people, of whom 484 were children.

To contain the spread of infection, the government of the Udmurt Republic purchased 10 000 doses of measles vaccine. Vaccination against measles is free of charge, regardless of age, in local hospitals.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

The Republic of Udmurtia is a federal subject of Russia. Its capital is the city of Izhevsk, which has a population: 1 521 420. The republic is located in the eastern portion of the Eastern European Plain, between the Kama and Vyatka Rivers. Its location can be seen on the maps at: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Udmurtia. A HealthMap ProMED-mail map can been found at http://healthmap.org/r/2bxi. - Mod.CP]

