[6] Ukraine
Date: Mon 23 Apr 2012
Source: Interfax.com.ua [in Russian, machine trans. abridged, edited]
http://www.interfax.com.ua/rus/main/101755


As of 19 Apr 2012, 7997 cases of measles have been recorded in Ukraine according to the press service of the Ukrainian Ministry of Health. Last night [22 Apr 2012], the Ministry of Health reported another 95 suspected cases, mostly in: Ivano-Frankivsk region - 26, Transcarpathian region - 16, Ternopil oblast - 15, Lviv region - 9, Rivne region - 5, Volyn region - 3. Last night, another case of measles was reported in Kiev. Enhanced control measures have been implemented in these regions.

The State Sanitary and Epidemiological Service has recommended that foreign persons should be vaccinated against measles before visiting Ukraine during Euro 2012 [Football championship]. "We have recommended and sent information to the embassies of all countries that will be represented in Ukraine to be proactive and disseminate information about the unfavourable measles situation in Ukraine. First Deputy Chairman Alexander Kravchuk also recommended that fans of the home country should ensure they have been vaccinated to provide cross-protection, reducing the probability of further introduction of measles virus infection into Ukraine and spread of infection by visitors returning to their own countries after the end of the tournament. According to the Minister, 93 sanitary and quarantine stations have been established in collaboration with the corresponding Polish authorities, as well as sharing of information concerning fans commuting between the 2 countries during the tournament.

In addition, teams of epidemiologists will be stationed at the stadium used during the tournament. However, the minister expressed his conviction that the Ukrainian epidemic control system would be adequate to respond to all the challenges that might arise during the staging of the tournament.

